EU’s Almunia Says More Banks May Need to Be Recapitalized

-- B y   J o n e s   H a y d e n
-- 
2011-09-20T11:24:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/eu-s-almunia-says-more-banks-may-need-to-be-recapitalized.html
European Union Competition
Commissioner  Joaquin Almunia  said more banks may need to be
recapitalized.  “As the sovereign debt crisis worsens, more banks may need
to be recapitalized,” Almunia said today in Brussels. “That’s
why its so important to solve the sovereign-debt crisis without
a delay.” Without a solution, “the bill will only grow
bigger,” he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jones Hayden at 
 jhayden1@bloomberg.net  